  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>During an inventory count, you can save your progress and resume later or make changes to an assigned count. Saved counts are specific to the staff member who performed the count, the location where it was done, and the computer or device used. Managers have the flexibility to delete individual items in Counted status or mass-delete all items still in Counting status.</p><h3 id=\"InventoryCounts:Pausing,Reassigning,andDeletingCounts-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427464/Inventory+Count+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427464\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Count Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591186/Inventory+Counts+Cycle+Counts+Unassigned+Counts\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932591186\" data-linked-resource-version=\"14\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Counts: Cycle Counts / Unassigned Counts</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1930494567/Inventory+Counts+Performing+an+Assigned+Count\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1930494567\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Counts: Performing an Assigned Count</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591200/Inventory+Counts+Pausing+Reassigning+and+Deleting+Counts\">Inventory Counts: Pausing, Reassigning, and Deleting Counts</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932558411/Inventory+Count+Process+Reconciling+Counts\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932558411\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Counts: Reconciling Counts</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"InventoryCounts:Pausing,Reassigning,andDeletingCounts-PausingCounts\">Pausing Counts</h2><p>If you need to pause and continue your inventory count later, click <strong>Save for Later</strong> at the bottom of your Counted Items list. The saved count will be specific to the staff member who performed the count, the location where it was done, and the computer or device used.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"InventoryCounts:Pausing,Reassigning,andDeletingCounts-ContinuingaSavedCount\">Continuing a Saved Count</h2><p>To access a saved count sheet, the same user must log in at the location where the count was performed, using the device where the count was originally saved. To view your Count List, go to <strong>Inventory \u2192 Inventory Counts</strong>. On the Inventory Count page, click the <strong>Count</strong> button. This will bring you back to your Count Sheet, where you can see your Counted Items list.</p><p>When you are ready to finish and submit your count, click <strong>Save &amp; Submit</strong>. This will move the items to <strong>Counted</strong> status. Counted totals are only visible by an Inventory Manager role or higher and are ready for reconciliation.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%203.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"InventoryCounts:Pausing,Reassigning,andDeletingCounts-DeletingCounts\">Deleting Counts</h2><p>A manager can delete individual items or all items in Counted status from the Inventory Count Summary page.</p><h3 id=\"InventoryCounts:Pausing,Reassigning,andDeletingCounts-DeleteIndividualItems\">Delete Individual Items</h3><p>Locate the item you want to edit, then click the <strong>Options</strong> button under the Actions column next to the item to expand additional options. From the list of available options, click <strong>Delete</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%206.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"204\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%207.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"InventoryCounts:Pausing,Reassigning,andDeletingCounts-DeleteAllCounts\">Delete All Counts</h3><p>A manager can mass-delete all counts in <strong>Counting</strong> status by clicking the<strong> Options button</strong> on the right side of the Inventory Counts Summary page. From the list of available options, click <strong>Cancel</strong> <strong>All</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"264\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%205.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"InventoryCounts:Pausing,Reassigning,andDeletingCounts-ReassigningInventoryCounts\">Reassigning Inventory Counts</h2><p>If you need to reassign a count to a different employee, a Manager can edit the count.</p><p /><p>On the Inventory Count Summary page, locate the item you want to edit. In the Actions column, click the <strong>Options</strong> button next to the line item to reveal additional options. From the list of options, click <strong>Edit</strong> to update the current assignment settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%2011.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"264\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%2012.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>You can reassign the Manager, Assignee, Due Date, and resolve Conflicts. Once you\u2019ve made changes, click <strong>Edit Count</strong> to update the count assignment.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932591200/Pause%208.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Location</strong>- Select the store location where the count will be performed.</p></li><li><p><strong>Manager</strong>- The assigned manager who will reconcile the counts when completed.</p></li><li><p><strong>Assignee</strong>- Select the staff member the count will be assigned.</p></li><li><p><strong>Due Date</strong>- Set the date and time the count needs to be completed.</p></li><li><p><strong>Conflicts</strong>- Select the appropriate conflict resolution for multiple assignees counting the same items:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Re-assign any pending counts to this staff member</strong> - If any of these items are already assigned to another staff member, they will be reassigned to the current staff member selected.</p></li><li><p><strong>Skip items already assigned to another staff member</strong> - If any of these items are already assigned to another staff member, it will leave them assigned to the original person and skip an assignment. This will help reduce duplicate item counts being assigned to multiple people.</p></li><li><p><strong>Allow both staff members to count the same item</strong> - New counts will be created and assigned to the new staff member while keeping any previous count assignment for this item. This may cause you to have duplicate item assignments in your Inventory Count Summary. We recommend this option only if you plan to compare <strong>Counted</strong> totals between staff members and delete the inaccurate count.</p></li></ul></li></ul><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
